attributes.description:
The Jeep Grand Cherokee's silhouette is no stranger to wilderness trails or metropolitan highways. As one of the first mainstream SUVs to hit the market back in the early '90s, the Grand Cherokee has long been a popular choice for people wanting a vehicle that possesses both off-road prowess and respectable urban civility. The 2010 Jeep Grand Cherokee stays close to its off-roading roots thanks to an advanced four-wheel-drive system, and for the most part, it's reliable, comfy and quick with its crazy amount of torque sitting at 510NM, now that’s an absolute beast!
Get in contact with us today about this iconic car.
